(179, 'Toontrack - Alchemy of Pop EZX - torrent', '2024', '12.69 gb', 'win-mac', 'audio ezdrummer librerias ezx', 'Alchemy of Pop EZX\n\npicPublisher : Toontrack\nWebsite : www.toontrack.com/product/alchemy-of-pop-ezx/\nFormat : SOUNDBANK\nQuality : 24 bit 44.1 kHz stereo\nDescription : Just as the alchemists of old tried to achieve magic by combining disparate elements, this EZX combines timeless vintage charm with cutting-edge electronic sound design. The result is a complex blend of drums and percussion that seamlessly transitions into a related yet expansive collection of kits for every aspect of popular music imaginable. If you\'re looking for the perfect potion for your productions, this expansion for EZdrummer 3 and Superior Drummer 3 is pure pop gold.\n\nThe Alchemy of Pop EZX was recorded by JUNO Award-winning engineer/producer/mixer Hill Kourkutis and sampled by drummer Skye Paulson (Digging Roots) at the famed Canterbury Music Company in Toronto, Ontario. Featuring four kits, each representing its own niche or style, as well as a wide collection of organic and electronic shakers, stomps, claps, clicks and effects tailored to each kit, it\'s an EZX that bridges the gap between multiple sonic ideals and delivers a canopy of kits that run the gamut from raw, rich, dark, earthy and open to subdued, tight and punchy.\n\nIn addition to using classic drumsticks, one set was recorded with brushes, one with mallets, and two sets were carefully muffled with towels. All this together gives you a unique palette of colorful sets for both intimate acoustics and hard-hitting percussives.\n\nWith Kourkutis\' past-inspired yet future-focused production style and Paulson\'s deep, swampy, pocket-sized groove style featured in the included MIDI library, this EZX will give you uncanny percussion fusion that\'s firmly rooted in vintage style but pushes today\'s sonic ideas into the future.\n\nIf you\'re looking to add some new pocket power to your pop productions, this EZX is your new go-to.\n\nPerfect for everything from rootsy beats to pocket-sized, edgy pop\nRecorded by JUNO Award-winning engineer/producer/mixer Hill Kourkutis\nSampled by drummer Skye Paulson\nRecorded at Canterbury Music Company in Toronto, Ontario\nFour unique drum kits sampled with drumsticks\nIncludes kit configurations sampled as regular, damped, and with mallets and brushes\nA total of 12 unique snares (some of which were recorded using different instruments or damping)\nIncludes custom electronic and acoustic one-shots hand-picked for each kit\nIncludes a MIDI library unique to this EZX (performed by sampling drummer Skye Paulson)\n\n!!!!ATTENTION ADDED FOLDER WITH MIDI!!!', NULL, 'https://digistorage.net/wx2u0n1x', 'music', 'ezx libreria', '2025-08-14', '345345', '2025-08-14 11:57:38', '2025-10-16 13:58:42', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
