(182, 'Latin Cuban Drums EZX - torrent', '2020', '2.81 gb', 'win-mac', 'ezx libreria ezdrummer', 'Latin Cuban Drums EZX\n\npicPublisher : Toontrack\nWebsite : Toontrack\nFormat : SOUNDBANK\nQuality : 24 bit 44.1 kHz stereo\nDescription : While rhythm may be the heartbeat of most genres, in Latin music the pulse and beat are the very life force. In fact, in many ways the groove is the song. Lovers, come and rock, dance and play! Cuba is always with you!', NULL, 'https://digistorage.net/sz65c6bz', 'music', 'ezx ezdrummer', '2025-08-14', '535345', '2025-08-14 12:38:18', '2025-10-16 13:58:42', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(183, 'Modern Metal EZX (ezdrummer) - torrent', '2022', '3.46 gb', 'win-mac', 'ezx libreria ezdrummer', 'Toontrack - Modern Metal EZX (SOUNDBANK)\n\npicPublisher : Toontrack\nWebsite : Toontrack\nFormat : SOUNDBANK\nQuality : 16 bit 44.1 kHz stereo\nDescription : Recorded by Will Putney at his own Graphic Nature Audio Studios in New Jersey, Modern Metal EZX\nis a comprehensive metal drum sound - suitable for anything from hardcore to metal and any subgenre in between.\n\nThe library is provided by the releaser in its original form, as it comes from the manufacturer. It is intended for installation in the system using the original installer present in the distribution. If you want to copy the library content to the folder with the rest of the libraries manually without the help of the installer, then you do this at your own risk, with a full understanding of what exactly and where you are copying. For old-timers, this will not be a problem. For others, it is highly recommended to use the installer.\n\ntimcrystal', NULL, 'https://digistorage.net/lsqobmc0', 'music', 'ezx ezdrummer', '2025-08-14', '45646456', '2025-08-14 12:40:29', '2025-10-16 13:58:42', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(184, 'The Classic EZX (ezdrummer) - torrent', '2020', '1.79 gb', 'win-mac', 'ezx libreria ezdrummer', 'Publisher : Toontrack\nWebsite : Toontrack\nFormat : SOUNDBANK\nQuality : 24 bit 44.1 kHz stereo\nDescription : Classic EZX is a modern drum sound library that combines everything good about modern recording techniques with the sound of the classic Helios recording console. This rare piece of equipment is known to have shaped the production on albums by bands like The Rolling Stones, Led Zeppelin and The Who. Yet after nearly 40 years of existence, it is considered one of the best sounds of all time.\n\nWorks with EZdrummer v1.4 or Superior Drummer v2.3 and higher!\nAdditional information\nThe Classic EZX was recorded by award-winning engineer Peter Henderson (Paul McCartney, Rush, Frank Zappa) and drummer Chris Whitten (Edie Brickell, The Waterboys) at the classic Shorefire Recording Studio in New Jersey. It comes with three (3) complete kits with several choices for alternative instruments – all perfectly tuned, handpicked instruments. The Classic EZX also presents a unique feature in the form of giving you two different setups; one contemporary multiple microphone and one with only four microphones, a so called “4 mic setup”. This setup is what helped shape the unique and organic production on many big albums of the 1970s – a sound that is making an evident resurgence in the music at the top of the charts of today.\n\nBe it a slamming 1970s rock song or a slim and tight contemporary pop track – the sounds of The Classic EZX will sit right in any mix.\n\nFEATURE SPOTLIGHT\n- Produced and recorded by Peter Henderson (Paul McCartney, Rush) and Chris Whitten (Edie Brickell, The Waterboys).\n- Two recording setups\n- Three (3) complete kits with additional instrument choices\n- Yamaha, Noble & Cooley and Craviotto drums\n- Large assortment of cymbals\n- Included MIDI library', NULL, 'https://digistorage.net/jk45c8dw', 'music', 'ezx ezdrummer', '2025-08-14', '3534543', '2025-08-14 12:42:14', '2025-10-16 13:58:42', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(185, 'Kick & Snares EZX (ezdrummer) torrent', '2022', '4.72 gb', 'win-mac', 'ezx libreria ezdrummer', 'Publisher : Toontrack\nWebsite : www.toontrack.com/product/kicks-snares-ezx/\nFormat : SOUNDBANK\nQuality : 24 bit 48 kHz stereo\nDescription : No matter the genre or style, probably any engineer will agree: the kick drum and snare drum are the two main instruments not only of the rhythm section, but of the entire mix. Kicks & Snares EZX represents exactly that. A total of 74 multi-sampled and previously unreleased instruments, recorded in eight different leading studios in Australia and the UK. Taking into account the wide range of alternative tunings and recorded configurations, you will have around 130 unique sounds. What makes this EZX even different from the previous ones is that each kick position has four additional channels with individually processed versions: Sub, Skin Low, Skin Hi and Club/Stick. This will allow you to endlessly customize and find your own personal mixes for each instrument. Additionally, Kicks & Snares EZX includes nearly 100 unique presets, covering everything from traditional/organic mixes to those that incorporate complex sound design.\n', NULL, 'https://digistorage.net/vnadflzj', 'music', 'TOONTRACK', '2025-08-14', '4645645', '2025-08-14 12:45:32', '2025-10-16 22:30:20', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(186, 'Classic Rock EZX (ezdrummer)', '2020', '4.25 gb ', 'win-mac', 'ezx libreria ezdrummer', 'Toontrack - Classic Rock EZX\npicPublisher : Toontrack\nWebsite : Toontrack\nFormat : SOUNDBANK\nQuality : 24 bit 44.1 kHz stereo\nDescription : Classic Rock EZX comes with two drum kits, plus several additional instruments and add-ons sourced from the Legacy of Rock SDX library , an expansion for Superior Drummer 3 recorded by legendary engineer/producer Eddie Kramer at AIR Studios in London, UK.', NULL, 'https://digistorage.net/y4kqx9hj', 'music', 'TOONTRACK', '2025-08-14', '3434534', '2025-08-14 12:47:24', '2025-10-16 22:26:25', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(187, 'Session HORNS PRO (brass) (kontakt)', '2020', '27.55 gb', 'kontakt', 'brass, audio, metales, trumpets, sax', 'Native Instruments - SESSION HORNS PRO v1.5.0\n\nPublisher : Native Instruments & e-instruments\nWebsite : Native Instruments or e-instruments\nFormat : KONTAKT (5.8+)\nQuality : 24 bit 44.1 kHz stereo\nDescription : Favorite pipes!\nIdeal for jazz, funk, disco and any light styles, and especially for frivolous styles.\nFor many years, this set remains one of the best libraries of pop-jazz brass instruments.\nSESSION HORNS PRO gives you three saxophones, two trombones, three trumpets, a tuba and a flugelhorn:\nFirst trumpet, second trumpet, mute trumpet, flugelhorn, trombone, bass trombone, tuba, alto sax, tenor sax, baritone sax\n38 preset sections for all popular styles will help you get started as quickly as possible.\nYou can assemble and customize the wind sections yourself, using up to six instruments divided into four voice registers.\nYou can also play solos on each instrument with maximum realism. 34 articulations will help you cope with it!', NULL, 'https://digistorage.net/svymwdo6', 'kontakt', 'brass, vst metales, brass', '2025-08-14', '356456456', '2025-08-14 12:50:59', '2025-10-18 19:38:08', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(188, 'Cinematic Studio Piano (kontakt)', '2020', '4.19 gb', 'kontakt', 'piano, kontakt', 'inematic Studio - Piano (KONTAKT)\n\npicPublisher : Cinematic Studio\nWebsite : cinematicstudioseries.com/piano.html\nFormat : KONTAKT\nDescription : Cinematic Studio Piano invites you to take a seat at the Yamaha C7 Grand on the world stage. You will be inspired by the warm, realistic sound of the instrument, recorded with condenser microphones using the same methods as the rest of the Cinematic Studio series. Intelligent scripts ensure maximum realism and versatility. The instrument uses the same simple graphical interface as the rest of the series. Its dynamism and realism make it the perfect accompaniment to the rest of our orchestral libraries. Great care was taken to capture the full dynamic range of the instrument. We also captured the occasional notes and pedal noises that occur during a real performance, adding greater authenticity to the sound. As with the rest of our libraries, the instrument has a no-nonsense interface that is easy to recognize, so you can get started straight away. Four microphone channels, controlled via a mixer, provide the perfect combination of detail and ambience. We\'ve also included various squeaks, glissandos and plucks as FX patches.\n', 'https://torre9.com/images/csp.jpg', 'https://digistorage.net/8fd2hjy0', 'kontakt', 'CINESAMPLES', '2025-08-14', '456456', '2025-08-14 12:53:26', '2025-10-17 10:37:40', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(189, '8Dio - The New Century Orchestral Series: Strings Lite Bundle kontakt', '2024', '31.57', 'kontakt', 'strings kontakt', '**8Dio - The New Century Orchestral Series: Strings Lite Bundle**\n\npicPublisher : 8Dio\nFormat : Kontakt (5.8.1+)\nQuality : Stereo 96 kHz 24 bits\nDescription : Strings collection: violins, violas, cellos and double basses\nOur flagship chamber strings collection. This is a new standard for deeply sampled, emotional strings.\nThis unique collection consists of four different chamber libraries.\n\nThe first is Ensemble Strings , a chamber ensemble of traditional strings, consisting of first violins (6 players), second violins (4 players), violas (5 players), cellos (4 players) and double basses (4 players).\n\nThe second is Sordino Strings , a chamber ensemble of muted strings. These are muted strings, with a silkier, darker tone. This is the largest collection of muted strings with a deep, emotional sound. Sordino Strings have a similar symmetry to Ensemble Strings , so both can be used as a single unit.\n\nThe third and fourth are two separate Ostinato Strings libraries . They are designed to offer you fully realistic repeating strings, something that is not possible with traditional multisamples, although we also offer a large number of these. Each of the two Ostinato Strings libraries features the same chamber string ensembles as the first two, but they focus on ostinatos and short notes. The first volume features traditional ostinatos, while the second volume focuses on more advanced ostinatos and rhythmic variations.\nCentury Strings was recorded in a new advanced environment that allowed us to have both raw (hall) and close (studio) sounding instruments. This means you have complete control over the room, from big, lush orchestral strings to studio-sounding instruments. Seven different microphone options include Mixed A, Mixed B, Decca, Wide and three close studio spot mics (Close 1-3).\n\nAll the legato articulations are dynamically layered on top of each other, and many of them have full control over vibrato. All the arcs are also velocity-based. Play softly and get soft arcs. Play harder and get more pronounced arcs. They were also recorded at different speeds, so they can elegantly complement your composition. And let\'s not forget the short notes, which were recorded so carefully that they may never need to be sampled again.\n\nThe new user interface ties everything together. Open the entire articulation menu with a few clicks. Get instant access to all mic and articulation controls. Century Strings contains all the articulations you would expect, plus a host of new and intelligently programmed patches.\nNew in version 2.0\n\nCentury Strings 2.0 is the largest and most complete update to any library collection we\'ve ever released. The update includes our new true polyphonic legato, 2 new mic positions in natural orchestral position, expanded articulation browsing, speed optimizations, and the Century Strings Lite add-on library .\n\nThe new True Polyphonic Legato is designed for both traditional, dynamically layered legato and our popular arcs. You can literally play as many notes as you want, whether it\'s a single melody with chords or strings playing in octaves. We call this Chord Legato. Our new, improved Arc Legato gives you the ability to play arcs with true polyphony, following the natural emotion and movement of arcs. We call this Poly-Time Legato.\n\nCentury Strings 2.0 also includes two specially created “on-location” mic mixes with instruments arranged in a traditional orchestral position. Mix A is a focused stage, while Mix B is a larger sound and is designed for large-scale blockbuster mixes. The different mix options for different instruments can help improve the separation of the sound, which is a great way to bring certain instruments to the forefront of your productions. We’ve also optimized the entire library, delivering more advanced features and superior performance across a range of workstations. The newly added chaos effects give you the ability to customize your signal flow and post-processing with over 140 impulse responses, stereo delay, EQ, and more.\n\nAdditionally, all owners of Century Ensemble Strings and Century Sordino Strings receive an updated version of Century Strings Lite , an additional notation tool in the collection that allows you to quickly notate entire string parts pre-loaded in natural orchestral positions.', NULL, 'https://digistorage.net/33jw0lij', 'kontakt', 'strings orchestra kontakt', '2025-08-14', '345345', '2025-08-14 12:56:12', '2025-10-16 15:41:11', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
