(238, 'Ample Guitar L 4.0Ample Sound - Ample Guitar L 4.0.0  picDeveloper : Ample Sound Version : 4.0.0 Release date : 09.09.2025 Format : Standalone, VST2, VST3, AAX, AU Medicine : present Bit depth : 64 bits System requirements : Windows 7+, macOS 10.15+ Descr', '2025', '4.56 gb', 'win-mac', 'Librería fe Guitarra Acústica 2025', 'Ample Sound - Ample Guitar L 4.0.0\n\npicDeveloper : Ample Sound\nVersion : 4.0.0\nRelease date : 09.09.2025\nFormat : Standalone, VST2, VST3, AAX, AU\nMedicine : present\nBit depth : 64 bits\nSystem requirements : Windows 7+, macOS 10.15+\nDescription : Classical guitar', 'https://torre9.com/images/agl.png', 'https://digistorage.net/0hmsvneb', 'music', 'AMPLESOUND', '2025-10-18', 'torrent', '2025-10-18 10:56:18', '2025-10-18 10:56:18', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(239, 'EBX Upright (Contrabajo real) vst, au', '2022', '577.9 mb', 'win-mac', 'De las mejores para jazz, acoutic pop, clásico, contrabajo vst, au', 'Publisher : Toontrack\nWebsite : Toontrack\nFormat : SOUNDBANK\nQuality : 24 bit 44.1 kHz stereo\n\nDescription : Upright EBX - Double bass, bass violin, cello, or, as in our case, upright bass. Despite its many names, it\'s one of those instruments that can be recognized by the sound of its notes. Slightly muted yet still vibrantly resonant, the earthy and dark timbre of the upright bass has permeated every layer of our musical history, from its first incarnation hundreds of years ago to the present day. It\'s the epitome of the perfect instrument for use in any jazz, rock, pop, or general acoustic composition.\n', 'https://torre9.com/images/ebxu.png ', 'https://digistorage.net/32tz8xkm', 'music', 'TOONTRACK', '2025-10-18', 'torrent', '2025-10-18 11:01:01', '2025-10-18 11:01:32', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(240, 'EBX Fretless para EZBass', '2022', '295.5 mb', 'win-mac', 'Excelente librería para EZBass bajo sin trastes muy real', 'Publisher : Toontrack\nWebsite : Toontrack\nFormat : SOUNDBANK\nQuality : 24 bit 44.1 kHz stereo\n\nDescription : At first glance, no one would have thought that removing the seemingly insignificant metal rods separating the notes on the bass guitar\'s fretboard would open up a completely new harmonic panorama and transform it into a virtually entirely new instrument. But it truly is. The sublime and high violin character, the almost weightless glissando, the rich, full, and heartfelt sustain, and the incredibly unique overall expressiveness—all these qualities make it impossible to confuse it with a traditional bass. Its subtle vibrato or simply the strike of a single note betrays it.\n\nThe Fretless EBX comes with a carefully selected instrument, sampled in maximum detail to capture all these unique characteristics. Beyond the sounds, it also includes a wide selection of presets and customizable MIDI content tailored to fretless playing styles.\n\nImmortalized by musicians like Sting, Les Claypool, Bernard Odum, Pino Palladino, Gary Willis, and, of course, Jaco Pastorius, the fretless bass has truly become a mythical creature in the bass world—revered for its tone but feared for its profound complexity. No matter what style you\'re playing, welcome to a bass that encompasses the full dynamic and tonal range needed to reach both ends. This is a bass that lets you paint with sound—outside the lines. Literally.\n\nMany thanks to rodderss2s for the material provided!', 'https://torre9.com/images/ebxf.png', 'https://digistorage.net/kofcebqd', 'music', 'TOONTRACK', '2025-10-18', 'torrent', '2025-10-18 11:04:08', '2025-10-18 11:04:46', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
