(251, 'AppCleaner - Quita programas de mac - Desinstalador', '2025', '85 mb', 'mac', 'Sirve para retirar programas o desinstalar sin dejar rastros, desinstaldor completo para mac', 'App Cleaner & Uninstaller 8.5.0.2\n\npicRelease year : 2025\nVersion : 8.5.0.2\nDeveloper : Nektony\nDeveloper\'s website : https://nektony.com/mac-app-cleaner\nPlatform : Intel/Apple Silicon Universal\nInterface language : English\nTablet : TNT\nSystem requirements : macOS 10.13 and above\n\nDescription : When you move macOS apps to the Trash, unfortunately, there may be resource files associated with the installation that remain where they are, unnecessarily cluttering your storage space.\n\nApp Cleaner & Uninstaller is a minimalist yet effective macOS app that can help you completely uninstall apps, reset an app to its first-run state by removing resource files, or detect all unused items left behind by previously uninstalled apps.\n\nScan your app and home folder to detect all installed apps.\nApp Cleaner & Uninstaller immediately begins the scan. In the main window, you can see a list of installed apps and a list of remaining resource files, organized into two separate tabs.\n\nSimply select one of the available entries and browse the list of associated application support files, caches, settings, or crash reports. Note that each item has a checkbox that you should select if you want to mark it for removal.\n\nFilter results and quickly identify old and large files.\nBy default, App Cleaner & Uninstaller displays all apps and remains sorted by name, but you can choose to display only old and large apps. This way, you can easily identify those that are taking up significant disk space, even if you don\'t use them, and act accordingly.\n\nIf you\'re unsure about removing a particular app, it can open the container folder in a Finder window so you can quickly check its usefulness.\n\nAn app cleaner that doesn\'t interfere with administrator-protected apps\n. To summarize, this utility can identify all installed apps along with associated service files, such as settings, logs, and cache files. You have the option to either uninstall apps or restore only the initial startup state by deleting resource files.\n\nIt\'s worth noting that App Cleaner & Uninstaller doesn\'t detect or support apps or resource files that require administrator permission to modify. This significantly reduces the risk of accidentally deleting something vital.', 'https://torre9.com/images/appcleaner.jpg', 'https://digistorage.net/p4505koz', 'aplicaciones', 'Nektony', '2025-10-18', 'dmg file', '2025-10-18 12:37:32', '2025-10-18 12:37:32', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
