(262, 'KORG - Legacy Collection 3 v10.2021 VSTi, AUi x64 (macOS)', '2024', '1.93 gb', 'mac', 'Excelente pack con los sintetizadores de korg clásicos, m1, wavestation y otros', 'Release year : 10.2021\nVersion : 2021.10\nDeveloper : KORG\nDeveloper\'s website : KORG\nPlatform : iNTEL\nFormat : STANDALONE, VSTi, AUi\nBit depth : 64bit\nInterface language : English\nTablet : present (KORG Software Pass + KeyGen) | R2R\nSystem requirements : Mac OS X 10.10 Yosemite or higher (latest update)\n- Intel Core 2 Duo or better (Core i5 or better recommended)\n- 4 GB RAM (8 GB or more recommended)\n- 2 GB free disk space (SSD recommended)\nDescription : In 2004, KORG released the KORG Legacy Collection, a groundbreaking attempt to faithfully recreate the company\'s most famous synthesizers in software. The KORG collection was updated in 2017 with the addition of the ARP Odyssey. In 2019, KORG Collection 2 was released, featuring a faithful recreation of the TRITON, along with updated graphical interfaces for all previous plug-ins.\nNow, in 2021, KORG Collection 3 introduces three new software products: KORG\'s first production analog synthesizer, the miniKORG 700S, the MOSS Tone Generator Prophecy, and the Triton Extreme, the pinnacle of vacuum tube music. The Triton series. KORG Collection 3 has now expanded to offer a captivating collection of iconic sounds from the 70s, 80s, 90s, and 2000s.\nA virtual instrument set and 1 effect:\nKORG ARP Odyssey v1.3.0 - Forty years later, a complete rebirth. A legendary analog synthesizer that defies its own age.\nThe ARP Odyssey was an analog synthesizer originally released in 1972 by American manufacturer ARP Instruments, Inc., which quickly garnered a loyal following among musicians. Ease of use and portability, the ARP Odyssey underwent several improvements throughout its history and remained in production until its discontinuation in 1981 due to economic difficulties and the digital revolution. Beloved by a wide range of musicians as a historical classic, its sound can be heard in numerous classic songs.\nKORG LegacyCell v1.6.0 is a virtual synthesizer that allows you to create combinations of two instruments (MS-20 and/or Polysix), two insert effects, and two master effects (a total of 19 algorithms: compressor, limiter, overdrive, equalizer, flanger, phaser, chorus, delay, reverb, etc.). You can layer sounds (with dynamic layer switching), create keyboard zones, and assign controllers to control instrument and effect parameters.\nKorg M1v.2.2.1 - This instrument needs no introduction - it\'s a classic of electronic (and other) music. Created in the mid-1980s, it has its own distinctive style, signature, and unforgettable piano preset that\'s unmistakable, a favorite among virtually all electronic musicians.\nKorg MDE-X v.2.2.0 - This multi-effects plug-in contains 19 high-quality effects sourced from Korg digital recorders, workstations, synthesizers, and standalone effects. They\'re a perfect complement to any synthesizer in the Korg Legacy Collection and a great addition to any computer setup.\nKORG miniKORG v1.0.1 - The miniKORG 700S, an improved version with an additional VCO, has been announced, and it\'s now recreated as a software instrument.\nThe miniKORG 700S is an exact replica of the original analog hardware with powerful new features only available in software.\nNow you can enjoy the unique sounds and capabilities of this historic KORG synthesizer on your computer.\nKorg Monopoly v.2.2.0, which went on sale in 1981, is considered the culmination of Korg\'s experience in creating analog synthesizers. It was released simultaneously with the Polysix, and these two instruments sparked a revolution in the world of synthesizers. Many musicians considered the Mono/Poly to be the best Korg synthesizer, with a number of unique characteristics.\nKorg MS20 v.2.2.1 - a software synthesizer that provides a complete imitation of its legendary original. In addition, it offers such advantages as modern polyphony up to 32 voices and 16-voice unison. Flexible external modulation settings and MIDI clock synchronization have also been added, providing even greater creative potential.\nKorg Polysix v.2.2.1 - emulates the six-voice analog polyphonic\nsynthesizer of the same name, the Korg Polysix, produced since 1981. With its full-voice sound architecture, chorus/phaser/ensemble effects, and a host of performance features (chord memory, arpeggiator, and unison), the Korg Polysix became an instant worldwide hit. Its instantly recognizable string and pad sounds remain deservedly popular.\nKORG Prophecyv1.0.2 - In the 1990s, PCM synthesizers were at the peak of their popularity, but club artists were already seeking a more flexible analog sound, hinting at the coming analog revival of the 2000s. It was in this context that Prophecy was announced in 1995, offering greater flexibility and tonal possibilities than ever heard before. Featuring advanced digital signal processing technology and a DSP chip previously used exclusively for effects processing, the Prophecy Solo Synthesizer is now available as a software plug-in with the ease of use, polyphony, and modern features essential for modern music production.\nKORG TRITON Extreme v1.0.2 - The last masterpiece of the 20th century, reborn after 20 years. A perfect reproduction of the TRITON workstation in software.\nKORG TRITON v1.3.3 - An exact copy of a keyboard workstation\nAccording to Korg, the virtual Triton is an exact replica of the real instrument, transferring both the capabilities of a workstation and a sampler to a digital environment. The virtual Korg Triton is equipped with a copy of the HI Synthesis (Hyper Integrated Synthesis) engine, as well as 4,000 presets and presets (both original and those released on expansion cards). As the company notes, each preset sounds completely identical to a real keyboard workstation.\nKorg WAVESTATION v.2.0.3 is a software reincarnation of the 1990 instrument, the technology of which has won numerous awards and crowds of fans around the world. All these features are also implemented in the software version: Advanced Vector Synthesis technology: mixing 4 sound sources with a joystick and Wave Sequencing - wavetable synthesis', 'https://torre9.com/images/korg.png', 'https://digistorage.net/ex8zc5z8', 'music', 'KORG', '2025-10-20', 'torrent', '2025-10-20 08:27:21', '2025-10-20 08:27:21', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
(263, 'KORG - TRITON Extreme 1.0.0 STANDALONE, VSTi, AUi (mac0S)', '2022', '1 gb', 'mac', 'Excelente sintetizador muy completo con muchos sonidos vintage y sintetizadores editables ', 'Release year : 2021\nVersion : 1.0.0\nDeveloper : KORG\nDeveloper\'s website : korg\nPlatform : iNTEL+M1\nInterface language : English\nTablet : cured (install and work) | MORiA\nSystem requirements : REQ: [iNTEL] + [M1]\nPlugin Formats: AU | VST | Standalone\nDescription : The last masterpiece of the 20th century, revived after 20 years. A perfect reproduction of the TRITON workstation in software.\nThis year, for the 20th anniversary of its release, KORG TRITON will finally be realized in software as KORG Collection TRITON. The plug-in accurately reproduces the HI (Hyper Integrated) synthesis system down to the smallest detail and contains each of the huge number of preset programs. Restore the true masterpiece sound that characterizes many hits.', 'https://torre9.com/images/korg.png', 'https://digistorage.net/hmo9muz5', 'music', 'KORG', '2025-10-20', 'dmg file', '2025-10-20 08:31:16', '2025-10-20 08:31:16', NULL, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
